<h2>uuid (universally unique identifier)</h2>
    <p>This attribute is used to modify component, class, category or interface. Global unique identifier is used to identify component, class, category or interface. The syntax is: uuid(UUID), of which UUID is the 128-bit integer generated by using the <a class="style1" href="../../../../environment/use_sdk/tools/ms_tools/uuidgen.htm">uuidgen</a> tool. For example: </p>
    <pre class="code">
[
    <b>uuid</b>(b7feb75f-0318-4dfd-828b-24c0bf16dd80),  //uuid of component UuidDemo
    uunm(http://www.koretide.com/car/UuidDemo.dll)
]
component UuidDemo
{
    [<b>uuid</b>(4129aabd-806e-4697-8d5c-09f870f9bade)]  //interface IInterface uuid
    interface IInterface {
        ECODE Func([in] int i);
    }
    [<b>uuid</b>(ba8130ff-3fff-405f-8fa3-4bcc75e7a13c)]  //class CClass uuid
    class CClass {
        interface IInterface;
    }
    [<b>uuid</b>(ea10ac92-c114-4e67-a64b-1aa37192ee73)]  //category CCategory uuid
    category CCategory {
        interface IInterface;
    }
}
</pre>
    <p>In sample component UuidDemo, the UUID of component UuidDemo is b7feb75f-0318-4dfd-828b-24c0bf16dd80, the UUID of interface IInterface is 4129aabd-806e-4697-8d5c-09f870f9bade, the UUID of class CClass is ba8130ff-3fff-405f-8fa3-4bcc75e7a13c, the UUID of category CCategory is ea10ac92-c114-4e67-a64b-1aa37192ee73.</p>
    <p>UUID is a 128-bit integer,which can guarentee global uniquely and identifies each and every interface and class object. Under the network environment of millions of class objects,it can gurantee that CAR component cannot connect to the wrong component, interface and method.</p>
    <p>UUID used to identify component is called GUID(Globally&nbsp;Unique&nbsp;Identifier).UUID used to identify interface is called IID(Interface&nbsp;ID).UUID used to identify class is called CLSID(Class&nbsp;ID).UUID used to identify category is called CATID(Category&nbsp;ID). Elastos.SDK provides tools that can automatically generate UUID: <a class="style1" href="../../../../environment/use_sdk/tools/ms_tools/uuidgen.htm">uuidgen</a>.</p>
    <ul><font color="red"><b>Note: </b>When defining component, class, category and interface, the attribute must use uuid attribute and you need to keep the uniqueness of UUID.</font></ul>
